result.name: Yummy Noodle

reviews.text: Long lines during lunch for a reason. Good prices and great build your own noodle soups. My favourite is mixing the curry and cheese sauce bases and adding in whatever meat or veggies you want. I recommend the chicken steak which is served on the side and moist, crispy, and flavourful. Takeout is an option as well if you don't want to wait for a seat in the small restaurant. Owner and staff are really nice.
Favourite noodle place for lunch in Central

Good quality food for one of the cheaper restaurants in central. Does Chinese food with a few twists. Don't expect fine dining here and a few shortcuts will be taken, but for the price that's to be expected. Filling meal, served quickly and very strong tastes for a low price at decent quality!
Quality ok. Around 50 dollar per noodles. Consider it is in central. It is ok
